{{ NCAATeamSeason | Mode = football | Year = 2009 | Team = VMI Keydets | Logo = Virginia Military Institute logo.png | LogoSize = 100px | LogoAlt = | Image = | ImageSize = | ImageAlt = | Conference = Big South Conference | Division = | ShortConference = Big South | TSNRank = | FCSCoachRank = | Record = 2â9 | ConfRecord = 1â5 | WinsVacated = | WinsForfeited = | ConfWinsVacated = | ConfWinsForfeited = | HeadCoach = [[Sparky Woods]] | HCYear = 2nd | OffCoach = | OCYear = | DefCoach = | DCYear = | MVP = | MVPYear = | MVP2 = | MVP2Year = | Captain = | CaptainYear = | Captain2 = | Captain2Year = | Captain3 = | Captain3Year = | Captain4 = | Captain4Year = | OScheme = | DScheme = | StadiumArena = [[Alumni Memorial Field]] | Champion = | BowlTourney = | BowlTourneyResult = | ConfChamp = | ConfChampResult = }} {{2009 Big South football standings}} The '''2009 VMI Keydets football team''' represented the [[Virginia Military Institute]] during the [[2009 NCAA Division I FCS football season]]. It was VMI's 119th all-time football season which started in 1891. They competed in the [[Big South Conference]], and they were led by 2nd year head coach [[Sparky Woods]], who was appointed VMI's 30th head coach in 2008.<ref>http://www.vmikeydets.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=43758&SPID=3895&DB_OEM_ID=9800&ATCLID=1431676&Q_SEASON=2010</ref> VMI played its home games at [[Alumni Memorial Field]], as they still do ever since 1962.<ref>http://www.vmikeydets.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=9800&ATCLID=1357385</ref>
The Keydets kicked off the year by just defeating Robert Morris 14â13. Two losses followed to then-#6 [[2009 James Madison Dukes football team|James Madison]] and then-#1 [[2009 Richmond Spiders football team|Richmond]], 44â16 and 38â28, respectively. Three more losses followed to conference opponents {{cfb link|year=2009|team=Gardner-Webb Runnin' Bulldogs|title=Gardner-Webb}}, {{cfb link|year=2009|team=Coastal Carolina Chanticleers|title=Coastal Carolina}}, and [[2009 Stony Brook Seawolves football team|Stony Brook]]. The next week, VMI held off {{cfb link|year=2009|team=Presbyterian Blue Hose|title=Presbyterian}} for a 31â20 win. It would be their final win of the year, as the Keydets lost to {{cfb link|year=2009|team=Charleston Southern Buccaneers|title=Charleston Southern}}, {{cfb link|year=2009|team=Liberty Flames|title=Liberty}}, [[2009 Army Black Knights football team|Army]], and [[2009 Old Dominion Monarchs football team|Old Dominion]].<ref>http://www.vmikeydets.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPSID=43759&SPID=3895&DB_OEM_ID=9800&KEY=&Q_SEASON=2009</ref> VMI finished 2â9 overall and 1â5 in the Big South.
